		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Mon, Mar 28th 1:12 AM2005 </span><span class="notbold">| <span class="sm">IP: Logged</span> | <a class="sm" href="/forum.html?forum=1&mid=111198705221414760&num=2&post=1&replyto=111199069739292398"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." height="11" width="17" /> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=111199069739292398></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span class="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=12888"><span id="Sage">tweelisT the Venerable</span></a><b><span id="Sage"><br>Sage</span></b><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />205 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.29]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=tweelisT&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%">
<p>I'd suggest heading to some place like HoH and snare kiting. Use the mage water pet for maximum damage (backstabbing). Have the ranger keep aggro but do NOT get withing melee range of the mobs. Duoing in HoH should get you xp pretty quick with the added bonus of ethereal/spectral parchments. <br /> <br />As for SCM3....very good idea for the mage. According to <a href="http://eq1.eqsummoners.com/" title="http://eq1.eqsummoners.com/" target="akztarg">http://eq1.eqsummoners.com/</a> SOE will be adding other pet focus items in the game so it may or may not be worth it to get the DPoC depending on when the focus items are added. <br /> <br />What I would recommend is have the mage pull with your highest level malo spell then sending your ranger to snare (and grab aggro) then have the pet pummel the mobs. Make sure you turn your pet taunt off. Once the ranger has sufficient aggro, start nuking with your mage. <br /> <br />If you can, get a mount. It'll help a lot with downtime and mana regen.</p>
